703667f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - State Street
703667f-a.text:
169-175 Clinton Street, east side, south from State Street, seen across
lot on State Street.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
703667f-a.folder: Clinton Street & State Street, Brooklyn, NY

706861f-a.title: Brooklyn: State Street - Clinton Street
706861f-a.text:
(1)
111-121 State Street, north side, between Clinton Street (right),
and Sidney Plaoe, as s een across clearing upon which once stood the
U.S. Apartments The corner building has no numerical designation.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, a more limited view of No. 1, showing also the rears of
the south side of State Street. Also shown, is the cleared site upon
which stood the U.S. Apartments, on the west side of Clinton Street, be-
tween Atlantic Ave., and State Street.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
706861f-a.folder: State Street & Clinton Street, Brooklyn, NY

703669f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - State Street
703669f-a.text:
Clinton Street, west side, between State Street and Atlantic Ave,
showing lot where once stood the United States Apartments, Brooklyn's first
large apartment house. Also seen is State Street, west of Clinton Street,
showing rear views of houses on south side.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

703665f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - State Street
703665f-a.text:
165-171 Clinton Street, east side, at State Street. 165-167 are at
the left, north of State Street. Also seen is State Street, north side, east
from Clinton Street.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
